{
  "stem": "2996.5",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This one for, this-- so we used it for-- we defied-- we defeated Jack Tenney.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Jack-- Senator Jack Tenney, who then represented the entire county of Los Angeles up in Sacramento as a Senator, was the head of the un-American Activities Committee.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he swallowed the-- the protocols of the elders of Zion and became a running mate for-- for Gerald LK Smith.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He-- Smith for Vice President, he Tenney for-- for for-- he ran for President, and Tenney for Vice President.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we defeated him.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But 'we' does not mean now the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We couldn't touch politics, because of the nations, right?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We did this over there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we had some people sitting on the school board who were [INAUDIBLE], who did not permit teaches to talk about the United Nations, about Eleanor Roosevelt, about the human-- the declaration of human rights, which was a product of that communist Eleanor Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And encouraged kids to tell the management in our schools that teacher so and so talked nicely about the United Nations or Eleanor Roosevelt.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We defeated all of them, but not as the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, this was separate, because we took our heads off and put different heads on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This was some of the important things.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well practically the anti-Nazi work was finished, but then the race relations work was increased.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think we accomplished more, far more, than the NAACP and the Urban League, and a couple of others like that.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, we had more money.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Secondly, there was too much conflict between the individuals and between groups.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were really responsible for the destruction of the organization about four years ago.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
